public interface DomainComparator
extends java.util.Comparator<java.lang.Object>, DomainPlugIn

A comparator interface for domain data. This interface just takes the standard java.util.Comparator interface and combines it with the domain plug-in interface. Implementations of this plug-in interface are used to control the sort order of lists of data.

This interface should not be implemented directly. Instead, custom plug-in classes should extend an existing comparator plug-in implementation or extend the curam.util.client.domain.compare.AbstractComparator class.

The locale and the domain information is accessible via the PlugIn.getLocale() and DomainPlugIn.getDomain() methods respectively.
